OL,3,CGordon Lyons defends meeting group
OL,4,Clinked to loyalist paramilitaries
OL,6,FCommunities Minister Gordon Lyons has
OL,7,Fdefended his decision to meet with a
OL,8,Fgroup which represents loyalist
OL,9,Fparamilitaries.
OL,11,FMr Lyons was one of two DUP ministers
OL,12,Fwho faced criticism after holding
OL,13,Fseparate meetings with the LCC, which
OL,14,Fincludes representatives of the Ulster
OL,15,FVolunteer Force, Ulster Defence
OL,16,FAssociation and Red Hand Commando.
OL,18,FEducation Minister Paul Givan also met
OL,19,Fthe umbrella group in September.
