OL,3,CGordon Lyons defends meeting group
OL,4,Clinked to loyalist paramilitaries
OL,6,FHowever, he told MLAs that he had made
OL,7,Fclear to the Loyalist Communities
OL,8,FCouncil (LCC) the importance of the
OL,9,Fdemocratic process, adding he had
OL,10,Falways been clear in his opposition to
OL,11,Fparamilitary violence.
OL,13,FThe minister said he had used the
OL,14,Fmeeting to "show what can be achieved
OL,15,Fthrough politics".
OL,17,FCommittee chairman Colm Gildernew
OL,18,Fasked why he chose to "engage with the
OL,19,FLCC on policy issues" while refusing
OL,20,Fto meet with other groups.
